category: International System of Units (SI) Base Units
explanation: Second, Meter, Kilogram, and Ampere are four of the seven fundamental SI base units. Fahrenheit is a unit of temperature measurement, but it is not an SI base unit; Kelvin is the SI base unit for temperature.

category: Seven Wonders of the Ancient World
explanation: The first four tokens are traditionally listed as four of the Seven Wonders of the Ancient World. The Acropolis of Athens, while a very significant ancient site, is not included in the traditional list of the Seven Wonders.

category: Musical Ensembles of Three or More
explanation: Trio, Quartet, Quintet, and Sextet refer to musical ensembles consisting of three, four, five, and six performers, respectively. Duet refers to an ensemble of two performers, making it the odd one out.
